<div id="slide2" class="slide">
  <div class="title">
    <h1>Different Types</h1>
    <ol>
      <li>Cyber Bullying - 
        This takes place over the internet in social media apps, direct message, email, and text. It can involve sharing harsh and mean words directly to someone, or leaving someone out. Here are a few ways to help prevent this form of bullying:
        <ul>
          <li> Report posts or comments that can be identified as bullying
          <li> Don't continue to leave people out of messages
          <li> Kindly confront the bully on the issue
        </ul>
        <br>
        
        <li>Verbal Bullying - 
         This tends to include namecalling or hurtful jokes that others join in on. Depending on what's being said, it can start off harmless and then begin to escalate into something that really hurts the target. Here are a few ways you can try to prevent this form of bullying:
          <ul>
            <li>Know the difference between a joke and being mean. Alot of the time people will laugh at something being said without realizing that the joke is hurting someone. Make sure it is harmless humor before joining in.
             <li>Confront the person being bullied. If you can tell that a joke is mean and the person is getting hurt, let them know that whatever mean things are being said aren't true and try to help rebuild their self esteem. 
               <li>Confront the bully. Sometimes the bully even isn't fully aware of how hurtful they are being. Let them know, and kindly tell them to stop.
          </ul> <br>
  </div>
