<h1>Information continued!</h1>
    <li>Social Bullying - 
            This includes mean looks, spreading false rumours, or being rude behind someone's back. The main purpose of this form of bullying is to damage someone's image. Here are a few ways to help stop it:
            <ul>
              <li>Don't join in. If you notice people are being mean to someone, don't add to the mean looks and gossip. Try to shut down any rude things that are being said.
                <li> As always, confront the bully, or bullies. With social bullying there tends to be more than one person picking on someone. Kindly tell them to stop and let them know that what they're saying isn't right.
            
    </ol>
   
